name: Hurst Public Library
directions: It's right after you enter the Youth Area of the library.  I usually see the READ poster of Ewan McGregor first.  It's right by the bathroom's door.
comment: The sign by the door says 'Family', but it's a restroom meant for anyone.  You won't be questioned for going into it without kids in tow.

name: Nick's Pizza
directions: Just ask nicely at the counter
comment: please consider purchasing something to support your local trans-owned business, but if you can't, it's not a problem

name: Nick's Pizza
directions: Just ask nicely at the counter

name: Target
directions: It's  the first door you see when you head toward the restrooms. It's unisex/family friendly.
comment: Yet another reason to love Target.

name: Tea Zone
directions: By the front of the shop
comment: Might have to buy something

name: Target In the Warwick mall
directions: If entering from the mall, it's all the way on the back right corner. If entering from the parking lot, it's immediately to your right.

name: Kroger
street: 2608 E Farm to Market Rd 544, W
directions: In the hallway next to the pharmacy and the jewelry shop there are two single room restrooms.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: The store is in a shopping center called Shoppes of Burnt Mills. Very easy to see. There's three unisex bathrooms in the way back

name: Which Wich?
directions: Through the front door to the back left
comment: Maybe stop for lunch, they have great vegetarian options too

name: Point Park University Student Center
directions: Second floor near the windows facing Boulevard of the Allies
comment: Front doors are unlocked by student ID key card access

name: Central Classroom Building
directions: On the third floor towards the west side of the building there are two gender neutral restrooms.

name: Archibald Sisters
directions: Ask for the key at the register. Its upstairs so sadly not handicap accessible.
comment: Super queer friendly business

name: The Rook and Pawn
directions: Walk straight in. Turn left. Walk all the way down the hallway and you'll see them.
comment: Don't necessarily need to be a paying customer. Just tell the bartender you're taking a look around because you've never been there before. Or just straight up ask if you can use the restroom! We're a safe space

name: In.gredients
directions: If you enter though the front door near the parking lot,take a left and then take a right. If you go to the backyard from the parking lot or gate,head straight back.
comment: If they ask you if you're going to buy anything you can mention that you're transgender and needed a safe place to go to the restroom,they're very supportive and even have a sign by their bathroom that says "This is a Gender-Neutral bathroom! Please feel free to use either one." (The last part is because there's 2 bathrooms) with their logo in the corner that instead of having their usual green backround has a rainbow one and they are active in supporting the lgbt+ community! :)

name: Vape Crusaders
directions: Second entrance, past the glass case on the right hand side.
comment: Just be polite, maybe ask about flavors if you vape, but if you ask to use the bathroom & don't seem "on illicit substances" they're chill about letting folks use the bathroom. It's always clean, too.

name: Multi-Faith Centre (UofT)
directions: Second floor, take a right when you come out of the elevator

name: Family court
directions: Just past the trial coordinator's area. It's a wheelchair accessible bathroom. But it's a self-contained room, and both genders may use it.
comment: You'll have to go through security to get to it, but they're nice.

name: Moffit Undergraduate Library 5th floor
comment: Need UC Berkeley student ID

name: Great Lakes Crossing Mall
directions: Central bank of restrooms includes Family Restroom with individual private restrooms.

name: The Painted Pot
directions: In the back of store.
comment: Open to public

name: Red Sauce Pizza
comment: Both restrooms are single person, locking. This is a safe space. If you need assistance, ask any staff.

name: Bistro Maxine
directions: At the back of the cafe
comment: For paying customers. It is a sit-down cafe but you may be able to order something small at the counter.

name: Fujishin Family Cellars

name: Caf√© Rio

name: Costa Vida
directions: Left side of the resteraunt on the far back wall.

name: Noodles and Company
directions: Behind big opaque glass wall that separates bathroom doors from the resteraunt space. Clean, safe. Also changing stations in both men/women's bathrooms.

name: Massage Envy
comment: for clients/customers

name: All that and a bag of chips
directions: Bottom floor past the game systems
comment: Girls gets in free to this buisiness, but the owner is a very nice man who would accommodate you.

name: The Bowllery
comment: Both are "all gender" restrooms.

name: Gossip Grill
directions: Straight back on the left side of the building
comment: Women's bathroom and unisex/gender neutral. Unisex bathroom has 2 urinals and a stall.

name: Gossip Grill
directions: Straight on back
comment: 21+ lady bar. There is usually a looooong line but there is one marked for "women" and another as "neutral," however people use both no problem.

name: Old Town Coffee Roasters
directions: To the right of the table with the creamer/sugar.
comment: Very small and hard to access but it is a single-room, single toilet, safe for trans.

name: Siuslaw River Coffee Roasters
directions: Past the drink counter, turn left. It's next to greeting card display.
comment: A single, completely enclosed restroom. It has a normal door, like you might find in a home, and is small, so it may not be accessible for everyone. It is a completely flat surface however.

name: Urban Mo's
directions: Just through the front entrance to the left.
comment: 21+, gay bar. Security never questions when we stop in to pee. Just need your ID to get in.

name: Nampa Public Library
directions: To the back left of the main floor in the children's area.
comment: 2 single "family" restrooms available.

name: Industrial Grind Coffee
directions: It is in the back of the cafe... ask first. They are very nice about letting people use it.
comment: They say that you don't need to buy any thing but I always do. It is an LGBT friendly business and the coffee is fantastic.

name: Sinclair Secondary School
directions: Main floor beside the office
comment: You have been be a staff member, student, or a signed in visitor at the office

name: Old main saloon
comment: Bar

name: Beach rose

name: DHS
